This paper focuses on detecting anomalies in Tor usage, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of data analysis techniques (cs.SI) and machine learning algorithms (cs.DS) to identify and rank anomalies. Additionally, the paper discusses the detection of internet censorship (cs.CY), which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the study of information control and suppression.
